duck: Aries (constellation) - Aries is one of the constellations of the zodiac, the groups of stars through which the apparent course of the sun passes during the year.

Aries (astrology) - Aries is the first astrological sign in the Zodiac, spanning the first 30 degrees of celestial longitude, which area the Sun transits, on average, between March 21 to April 21 each year.
A constellation in the Northern Hemisphere near Taurus and Pisces.
